// frame_quad.su — FOUR-REGION LAYOUT: four whole-frame widgets composed into the
// quadrants of one frame, on the substrate.
//
// GUI shapes increment — frame_layout.su generalized past two regions. The host
// passes three quadrant masks (m0 = top-left, m1 = top-right, m2 = bottom-left,
// coordinate-derived grid geometry like maskL); the substrate derives the fourth as
// the complement (m3 = 1 - m0 - m1 - m2, mirroring layout's maskR), so the four
// regions tile the frame with no overlap and no gap by construction. Composition is
// masked superposition over the four shape fields of this demo set:
//
//   quad = m0*glow + m1*ring + m2*diag + m3*checker
//
// all elementwise buffer arithmetic (hadamard + add), one substrate pass.
function vector quad(vector x, vector y, vector ones,
                     vector m0, vector m1, vector m2,
                     vector radius, vector half, vector px, vector py) {
    vector glow = ones - hadamard(x, x) - hadamard(y, y);
    vector r2 = hadamard(x, x) + hadamard(y, y);
    vector d = r2 - radius;
    vector ring = ones - hadamard(d, d);
    vector dg = hadamard(half, ones + hadamard(half, x + y));
    vector check = hadamard(half, ones + hadamard(px, py));
    vector m3 = ones - m0 - m1 - m2;
    return hadamard(m0, glow) + hadamard(m1, ring)
         + hadamard(m2, dg) + hadamard(m3, check);
}

// Sanity entry: m0 = 1 (top-left region) at the centre -> shows the glow = 1.
function vector main() {
    return quad(make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0), make_real(1.0),
                make_real(1.0), make_real(0.0), make_real(0.0),
                make_real(0.5), make_real(0.5), make_real(1.0), make_real(1.0));
}
